This plugin converts Greek characters in post, page and term slugs to Latin (Greeklish) characters. Also gives the option to regenate all permalinks.

== Description ==

This plugin converts Greek characters in post, page and term slugs to Latin characters. (Greeklish). It is very useful for creating human-readable and short URLs. This plugin is a "marriage" of Sandor Kovacs and Panagiotis Kontogiannis plugins.

= Features =
* Automatically converts existing post, page and term slugs on activation
* Saves existing post and page permalinks integrity
* Performs transliteration of attachment file names
* Includes Greek characters
* Transliteration table can be customized without editing the plugin itself.
* Regenerate old permalinks

== Installation ==

1. Upload plugin's folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory.
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.
3. Make sure your system has iconv set up right, or iconv is not installed at all. If you have any problems (trimmed slugs, strange characters, question marks) - please ask for support. 
4. That's it!

